The paper deals with upper bounds for rank metric codes, which are closely related to information theory and coding theory, hence the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of Ferrers diagrams, which are commonly used in combinatorics and discrete mathematics, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves the use of matrices and linear algebra, which are relevant to cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
